<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6588330>
    dc:description "1. Anderson’s Tuco-tuco (Clenomys andersoni), 2. Bicolored Tuco-tuco (Cltenomys bicolor), 3. Bolivian Tuco-tuco (Clenomys boliviensis), 4. Erika’s Tuco-tuco (Clenomys erikacuellarae), 5. Goodfellows’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys goodfellowi), 6. Natterer’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys nattereri), 7. Rondon’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys rondoni), 8. Steinbach’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys steinbachi), 9. Yates’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys yatesi), 10. Chacoan Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys conoveri), 11. Forest Tuco-tuco Citenomys ([ rater), 12. Lessa’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys lessai), 13. Lewis’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys lewis), 14. Long-tailed Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys fulvus), 15. Andean Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys opimus), 16. Salta Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys saltarius), 17. Scaglia’s Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys scagliai), 18. Argentine Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys argentinus), 19. Mottled Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys latro), 20. Furtive Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys occultus), 21. Tucuman Tuco-tuco (Clenomys tucumanus), 22. Brazilian Tuco-tuco (Ctenomys brasiliensis)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6588330/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

